# Confirmation dialog (`src/app/shared/confirm`)

Global imperative confirmation modal for destructive or irreversible actions. Do not build ad-hoc `window.confirm` or duplicate modal markup in feature pages.

## Structure

| File | Role |
|------|------|
| `confirm.constants.ts` | `CONFIRM_CANCEL_LABEL_KEY`, `CONFIRM_CONFIRM_LABEL_KEY` |
| `confirm.types.ts` | `ConfirmOptions` |
| `confirm.service.ts` | `confirm(options): Observable<boolean>` |
| `confirm-dialog/` | `ConfirmDialogComponent` — single host mounted in app root |
| `index.ts` | Barrel |

## Global host

`app.html` mounts `<app-confirm-dialog />` once (alongside `<router-outlet />`). Feature pages only inject `ConfirmService`; no per-page dialog template.

## API

```typescript
import { ConfirmService } from 'shared/confirm';
import { filter, switchMap, take } from 'rxjs';

this.confirmService
  .confirm({
    titleKey: '…',
    messageKey: '…',
    danger: true, // optional — red confirm button
    messageParams: { name: '…' }, // optional ngx-translate interpolation
    // confirmLabelKey / cancelLabelKey optional — see i18n below
  })
  .pipe(filter(Boolean), take(1), switchMap(() => this.api.delete(id)))
  .subscribe({ next: () => this.refresh() });
```

- Returns `Observable<boolean>` — `true` on confirm, `false` on cancel, backdrop click, or Escape.
- Only one dialog at a time; opening a new request dismisses the previous as cancelled.
- Async work runs **after** the modal closes (no in-modal loading state).

## i18n

| Path | Use for |
|------|---------|
| `shared.confirm.common.cancel` | Default cancel button (do not duplicate per feature) |
| `shared.confirm.common.confirm` | Default confirm button (do not duplicate per feature) |
| `…features.<feature>.table.deleteConfirm.title` | Feature-specific dialog title |
| `…features.<feature>.table.deleteConfirm.message` | Feature-specific dialog body |
| `shared.form.common.discardChanges.*` | Shared leave-form dialog copy (`PageBackLinkComponent`) |

Callers pass **title + message only** in most cases. Override `confirmLabelKey` / `cancelLabelKey` only when shared defaults are wrong for that flow.

## Styling

Theme tokens in `src/styles.scss` (see `theme-tokens.mdc`):

- `--bg-confirm-dialog` — aliases `--bg-surface` (solid in both themes)
- `--border-confirm-dialog`
- `--shadow-confirm-dialog`
- Primary button hover: `--bg-primary-hover` via `interactive-primary-btn` mixin — not opacity

Dialog `z-index: 250` (above mobile sidebar `200`). Body scroll locked while open.

## Example

Delete confirmation: `portal/admin/features/vehicles/table/vehicle-table-page.component.ts` — `ConfirmService` before `AdminVehicleService.delete`.

Leave form (dirty back link): `shared/ui/page-back-link/page-back-link.component.ts` — `ConfirmService` with `shared.form.common.discardChanges.*` before navigating to the list URL.

Do not use `window.confirm`. Do not add a second global dialog host.
